    <main>
      <h2>Inundation</h2>
      <p>The waves wash over me<br>
	Filling my every pore<br>
	Submerging my soul in saline sea
      </p>

      <p>
	Sand castles built over hours<br>
	Are destroyed in just seconds<br>
	Salt kills all shrubs, trees and flowers
      </p>

      <p>
	Gardens once teeming with art and life<br>
	Lay barren and featureless<br>
	Devoid of movement or strife
      </p>

      <p>
	The sun blazes down on the ocean's retreat<br>
	All signs of life taken under the deep<br>
	The soil cracks under the blistering heat
      </p>

      <p>
	Over and over the cycle repeats.
      </p>    
    </main>
